"},{"d":"तथा","m":"so also"},{"d":"अङ्गदः","m":"Angada"},{"d":"शैलशृङ्गाणि","m":"looked like mountains"},{"d":"गृहीत्वा","m":"taking"},{"d":"द्वारम्","m":"gate"},{"d":"अभ्ययुः","m":"marched."}]},{"v":39,"dev":"रामवाक्यमुपश्रुत्य हरयो जितकाशिनः ।पादपैरर्दयवनीरावानराःपरवाहिनीम्","trans":"The monkeys desiring to be triumphant, took trees and began to strike at the enemies on hearing Rama's control.","words":[{"d":"जितकाशिनः","m":"desiring to be triumphant"},{"d":"हरयः","m":"monkeys"},{"d":"रामवाक्यम्","m":"Rama's command"},{"d":"उपश्रुत्य","m":"hearing"},{"d":"वीराः","m":"heroes"},{"d":"वानराः","m":"Vanara"},{"d":"पादपैः","m":"trees"},{"d":"परवाहिनीम्","m":"enemies"},{"d":"अर्धयन्","m":"began to strike."}]},{"v":40,"dev":"ततोहरीणांतदनीकमुग्रंरराजशैलोद्यतदीप्तहस्तम् ।गिरेःसमीपानुगतंयथैवहन्महाम्भोधरजालमुग्रम्","trans":"Then Vanaras taking trees and mountains in their shining hand s marching close to each other seemed like a huge mass of terrible clouds hanging close to a mountain. ।।इत्यार्षेवाल्मीकीयेश्रीमद्रामायणेआदिकाव्येयुद्धकाण्डेषष्टितमस्सर्गः ।। This is the end of the sixty first sarga of Yuddha Kanda of the first epic the holy Ramayana composed by sage Valmiki.","words":[{"d":"ततः","m":"then"},{"d":"शैलोद्यतदीप्तहस्तम्","m":"taking trees and rocks in their shining hand s"},{"d":"हरीणाम्","m":"the Vanaras"},{"d":"उग्रम्","m":"front"},{"d":"तत्","m":"that"},{"d":"गिरेः","m":"mountain"},{"d":"समीपानुगतम्","m":"close to each other"},{"d":"उग्रम्","m":"terrible"},{"d":"महत्","m":"huge"},{"d":"महाम्भोधरजालंयथैव","m":"like mass of clouds hanging"},{"d":"रराज","m":"seemed."}]}]}